OL,7,FThat diagnosis has impacted her whole
OL,8,Flife. She lived in fear of an early
OL,9,Fdeath, planning her funeral in her
OL,10,Fearly 20s and telling me that there
OL,11,Fwas never a plan or goal to her life
OL,12,Fas she never expected to live for long
OL,13,Fenough to need one.
OL,15,FThe treatment to rid her of hepatitis
OL,16,Fruined her health, leaving her unable
OL,17,Fto work, and unable to have children.
OL,19,FAnd she feels guilt that she is alive,
OL,20,Fwhen so many friends she has met
OL,21,Fthrough support groups are not.
